claim.claim-text:
16. A method of tracking product level of a sheet product roll dispenser, the method comprising: providing a product level tracking system comprising: a product level sensor configured to move from a first position to a second position when a quantity of sheet product on a sheet product roll mounted within the sheet product dispenser is depleted below a threshold quantity;
determining, via the processor, one of occurrence of a high priority event or expiration of a pre-defined time interval; and, in response thereto: determining product level data indicative of a quantity of sheet product on the sheet product roll mounted in the sheet product dispenser; causing transmission of the product level data to a remote computing device; and causing resetting of a timer for determining expiration of the pre-defined time interval,
wherein the high priority event includes an event from a group of events including an instance in which the product level sensor moves to the second position.
